data.name: Cinnamon Waffles
data.quickTastyDescription: Fluffy and warm waffles infused with cinnamon, perfect for breakfast or brunch.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine the milk, eggs, melted butter, and vanilla extract. Mix well.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined; do not overmix.
Preheat your waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions.
Pour enough batter into the waffle iron to cover the surface. Close the lid and cook until golden brown, usually about 5 minutes.
Carefully remove the waffle and repeat with the remaining batter.
